Install Git on my Linux machine 
* sudo apt-get install git

Repo creation:
* mkdir Git
* git init Fun
* cd Fun

*Every time you want to access the Git
git config --global user.name "SFChanakya"
git config --global user.email "nraga@yahoo.com"
* To create a clone
git clone "https://www.github.com/SFChanakya/Fun.git"
# to Define the connection between your local and ORIGIN
git remote set-url origin  https://github.com/shirag/Fun.git
git re
# to Define the connection between your local and UPSTREAM
 git remote add upstream https://github.com/SFChanakya/Fun.git

* vi README
* git add README
* git commit -m "third commit"
* git remote add origin https://github.com/SFChanakya/Fun.git
* git push -u origin master

git status 
git add addTwoNumersFinal.cpp
git commit -m "Ashok Review Request" 
git push -u origin master

To show all branches present
*git branch -v

To create a new branch by name testRagha
*git checkout -b testRagha

To delete a local branch 
* git checkout master //switch to the master branch first
* git branch -d testRagha //delete the testRagha branch


git pull origin master
